(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The case against the man &nbsp;accused of killing Top Billing presenter Simba Mhere and his friend Kady-Shay O'Bryan is expected to resume &nbsp;in the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Monday.Preshalin Naidoo faces two charges of culpable homicide and additional charges of reckless or negligent driving, and inconsiderate driving. His VW Polo GTI crashed into Mhere's car on William Nicol Drive, Fourways, in the early hours of January 31, 2015.Mhere's father Joseph was also a passenger in the car. He survived. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.